{"label":"Node JS - Intro","id":"nodejs","list":[{"label":"Multiple Choice Question","type":"mcq","id":"test","commonData":{"title":"Multiple Choice Question","allowFrac":false},"data":[{"questions":[{"qText":"What is Node.js primarily used for?","options":"Running JavaScript on the server\n              Designing web pages\nCompiling Java code\nCreating mobile applications"},{"qText":"Node.js is built on which JavaScript engine?","options":"V8\nSpiderMonkey\nChakra\nNashorn"},{"qText":"Which of the following is true about Node.js?","options":"It runs single-threaded, non-blocking I/O operations.\n              It is synchronous by default.\nIt is a front-end framework.\nIt can only run on Linux."},{"qText":"Which module is used to create a web server in Node.js?","options":"http\nfs\nurl\nnet"},{"qText":"Which command initializes a new Node.js project with a package.json file?","options":"npm init\n              node init\nnpm start\nnode start"}]},{"questions":[{"qText":"Which of the following is used to import modules in Node.js (CommonJS syntax)?","options":"require('module')\n              import moduleName from 'module'\ninclude('module')\nload('module')"},{"qText":"What does the fs module in Node.js provide?","options":"File system operations\nFrontend styling\nFile compression\nFramework support"},{"qText":"Which of the following is NOT a built-in module in Node.js?","options":"express\n              os\npath\nevents"},{"qText":"Which command is used to install a package globally in Node.js?","options":"npm install -g packagename\nnpm install packagename\nnode install packagename\nnpm global add packagename"},{"qText":"What is the default scope of variables in Node.js modules?","options":"Module scope (private to the file)\n              Global\nFunction scope only\nPublic by default"}]},{"questions":[{"qText":"Which method is used to read files asynchronously in Node.js?","options":"fs.readFile()\nfs.readFileSync()\nfs.read()\nfs.openFile()"},{"qText":"Which statement about Node.js event-driven architecture is correct?","options":"Node.js uses an event loop to handle asynchronous operations.\nEvents are synchronous only.\nNode.js doesn't support event-driven programming.\nEvent-driven architecture slows down applications."},{"qText":"What is the purpose of package.json in Node.js?","options":"To store metadata and dependencies of the project\n              To style the project\nTo run the server\nTo secure the project"},{"qText":"How do you start a Node.js application named app.js?","options":"node app.js\nrun app.js\nnode start app.js\nnpm run app.js"},{"qText":"Which of the following best describes Node.js?","options":"Single-threaded, non-blocking I/O model\nMulti-threaded, blocking I/O model\nMulti-threaded, synchronous I/O model\nSingle-threaded, blocking I/O model"}]}]},{"label":"Drag and Drop","id":"dragdrop","type":"matchByDragDrop","data":{"fontSize":"1.3rem","dashWidth":80,"text":"Core module used to create a web server : *http module*\nPackage manager used to install and manage dependencies : *npm*\nExports functions/objects from a file so they can be reused : *module.exports*\nFunction used to import modules into a file : *require()*\nJavaScript runtime built on Chrome's V8 engine : *Node.js*\nProvides information and control over the current Node.js runtime : *process object*\nHandles asynchronous operations and non-blocking I/O : *Event Loop*\nCore module used to work with the file system : *fs module*"}},{"type":"classifySentence","label":"True or False","id":"true-false","data":{"title":"True or False","types":[{"name":"True","text":"Node.js allows running JavaScript code outside of a web browser.\n            The http module in Node.js is used to create web servers.\n            npm stands for Node Package Manager and is used to manage Node.js packages."},{"name":"False","text":"Node.js is multi-threaded by default.\n            Node.js cannot interact with the file system."}]}},{"id":"fillup","label":"Fill in the blanks","type":"fillup","data":{"title":"Fill in the blanks","fontSize":"1.4rem","text":"Node.js is built on the *V8 ( SpiderMonkey, Chakra) * JavaScript engine.\n        The command used to initialize a Node.js project is *npm init (node start, npm run)* .\n        To include a module in Node.js, we use the *require (import, include) * function.\n        The module used to work with the file system in Node.js is *fs (http, url )* .\n        Node.js uses a *non-blocking (blocking, synchronous) * model to handle I/O operations."}}]}